<module>
    <h>glé</h>
    <p><g>glé</g>
        <en>very</en> is a particle which intensifies a following <a
            href="?xx=adjectives/adjectives">adjective</a>.</p>

    <section id="forms">
        <h>forms</h>
        <p>Note that <g>glé</g> is usually spelled with a grave accent, as <g>glè</g>, in post-1970s
            Neo-Gaelic.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h>uses</h>
        <section>
            <h>specifier</h>
            <p><g>glé</g> is always used as the pre-specifier to a (gradeable) <a
                    href="?xx=adjectives/adjectives">adjective</a>, which it lenites.</p>
            <p>Some examples – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha an cù <m>glé luath</m>.</gd>
                        <tr>The dog is very swift.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 14</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha an seòmar <m>glé bhlàth</m>.</gd>
                        <tr>The room is very warm.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 14</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha mi <m>glé sgìth</m>.</gd>
                        <tr>I am very tired.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 14</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha Seumas <m>glé mhór</m>.</gd>
                        <tr>James is very big.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 14 [227]</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </section>
    </section>

</module>
